                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="200625" author="adilger" created="Thu, 29 Jun 2017 17:56:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Mahmoud, yes the &lt;tt&gt;readcache_max_filesize&lt;/tt&gt; tunable is the OST object size and not the file size.  The intention of this parameter is that it can be used to limit the read cache on the OSS to small files/objects, and avoid caching large files that are unlikely to be re-used and will overwhelm the cache.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="200592" author="mhanafi" created="Thu, 29 Jun 2017 14:28:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please fix typo in the heading.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
